raw_data.title: Agile Coach
raw_data.description: The Agile coach works directly with information technology or network project teams leading the development process and coaching the team on agile concepts. The Agile Coach will need to have a technical understanding of agile principals and the ability to communicate with stakeholders and middle management. The Agile coach coordinates the success of a information technology or network project team; educations that team and their Stakeholders on Agile principals and leads the communication for the team.

Project initiatives range from KM assessment and roadmap development to the execution of pilot programs including KM leadership development, taxonomy design, content strategy, search tool implementation, and collaboration enhancements.

raw_data.title: Change Management Expert

Recommend and collaboratively develops operating models for change in a complex environment; Owning the end-to-end process of stakeholder analysis, including facilitating focus groups and interviews, conducting analyses, and writing reports on findings; Leading discussions around change strategy, to include key messages and visioning; Cultivating and coaching communities to influence change; and delivering communications and training products as needed.

raw_data.title: Consultant
raw_data.description: Conduct requirements analysis through organized forums, focus groups, and surveys on Knowledge Management strategies. Design, test, and deploy new features, such as group collaboration web spaces and searchable photo collections, information assets, on the client’s website, network, systems. Provide support and enhancements to Knowledge Management applications for use on mobile platforms. Facilitate the incorporation of multimedia in Knowledge Management applications. Facilitate the roll out of Knowledge Management initiatives through demonstrations, presentations, training documentation, and training workshops. Develop training materials and train program staff on Knowledge Management areas such as information management, software use, and information management systems.

raw_data.title: Consultant, Principal
raw_data.description: The Knowledge Management Principal Consultant has responsibility for effective implementation of programs and activities that are part of the business unit’s KM strategy. The KM Principal Consultant develops and supports communities of practice and networks with peers. The KM Principal Consultant assesses knowledge management needs, develops strategies to meet those needs, identifies and obtains required resources, understands technologies/systems, and ensures access by the staff and management of the (Sector/Unit) and internal and external clients. The KM Principal Consultant keeps informed about knowledge management practices and manages outreach programs to inform Unit staff and external clients of KM resources and systems. The KM principal Consultant may direct staff and oversee consultants in executing specific tasks in his/her areas of responsibility.

raw_data.title: Consultant, Senior
raw_data.description: Accountable to provide standardized, documented processes and process solutions for the assigned business unit that are cost- effective and timely, and that comply with information technology management and architecture policies and procedures and requirements. Act as the key escalation point for new and/or revised processes, business issues, procedures, products and processes of a more complex nature, and apply in-depth process knowledge to ensure consistency and effectiveness of service and support and effective management. Act as a key control over critical business activities related to the area of expertise, with a significant involvement in analyzing and advising on business implications of options, to facilitate an effective and comprehensive understanding of business decisions and sound risk management.

raw_data.title: Content Analyst
raw_data.description: Assist in the implementation of the knowledge management program. This job is critical to ensuring requirements are accurately reflected and implemented to enable realization of the long-term goals. The Analyst is responsible for working closely with the cross-functional technology and business teams to ensure the solutions continue to support the day-to- day operations as well as the strategic vision. This role is key in ensuring knowledge transfer across the enterprise solutions and to guide business/procedural support teams of information assets. This role will support current and future solution initiatives and will build on their expertise as a solution subject matter expert. They will make strategic decisions on behalf of the team and ensure capabilities are developed to drive business value. They will also be responsible for providing inputs to develop the roadmap for solutions and will support the execution of the governance processes and procedures.

raw_data.title: Sharepoint Architect
raw_data.description: The SharePoint Architect will shape the strategy, architecture, methodology and standards for delivering SharePoint solutions. Develops and implements SharePoint policies, procedures, system governance rules/procedures, security administration and best practices. S/He will plan, lead, coordinate and execute projects on a global or regional scale. Interact with stakeholders to develop and deliver SharePoint solutions, ranging from SharePoint site creations to 3rd party application implementations, addressing business needs and opportunities. The SharePoint Architect manages, maintains and administers the SharePoint environment to ensure efficient operations (capacity planning, upgrades, patch application, system backups/restores, systems monitoring/availability and production of systems metrics and reports). raw_data.title: Taxonomist, Senior
raw_data.description: The Taxonomist will apply information architecture best practices to build a content structure that will meet the needs of both internal and external customers. S/He will develop product-based and topic-based content maps to that will be reflected in site search, browsing, and navigation experiences. Define the taxonomy hierarchy for knowledge base articles across all product areas. Use data and analytics to analyze existing content inventories and make recommendations to alleviate gaps and overlaps. Lead conversations with content stakeholders to find consensus and create timelines to take existing content and migrate it into a structured architecture. Develop, implement, and maintain guidelines and procedures for consistent and quality tag management and content organization. Monitor and report on key performance indicators to manage and understand key opportunities and impacts.

raw_data.title: UX Consultant
raw_data.description: Develop the optimal user interface design based upon studying users and employing industry best practices. Gather user requirements to support the functional and technical requirements. Conducts usability tests in which users are observed interacting with a preliminary design of the software/website. Observations from these tests are used to iterate and improve the design. Conducts expert reviews of user interfaces and provides feedback to ensure designs meet the mental model of a user. Observe users during their daily activities to better understand how proposed software will integrate. Works with users to understand desired features and functions of proposed software.
